6000|$|One day, {{while my}} husband was busily at work, I sat beside him reading an old cookery book called The Compleat Housewife: or Accomplish'd Gentlewoman's Companion. In the midst of {{receipts}} for [...] "Rabbits, and Chickens mumbled, Pickled Samphire, <b>Skirret</b> Pye, Baked Tansy," [...] and other forgotten delicacies, there were directions for the preparation of several lotions {{for the preservation of}} beauty. One of these was so charming that I interrupted my husband to read it aloud. [...] "Just what I wanted!" [...] he exclaimed; and the receipt for the [...] "Lily of the Valley Water" [...] was instantly incorporated into Kidnapped.|$|E
