5000|$|Sium sisarum, {{commonly}} known as <b>skirret,</b> is a perennial plant of the family Apiaceae sometimes grown as a root vegetable. The English name <b>skirret</b> {{is derived from the}} Middle English 'skirwhit' or 'skirwort', meaning 'white root'. In Scotland it is known as crummock. Its Danish name sukkerrod, Dutch name suikerwortel [...] and German name [...] "Zuckerwurzel" [...] translate as 'sugar root'.|$|E
